---
title: Housing Choice — Tenant Onboarding (Phase 1)
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor T as Tenant
    participant A as Housing Choice App
    participant S as Team
    Note over T,S: The app owns the phone number. Every message flows between Tenant and Team through the app (both directions).<br/>Notes marked [AUTO] are app automation. The team's messages are manual comms (Phase 1).
    alt Inbound by TEXT or PHONE CALL
        Note over T,A: Prospect saw a specific listing on affordablehousing.com
        alt By text
            T->>A: Text — is this property still available?
            Note over A: [AUTO] Log inbound text, create contact
            A->>S: Relay new lead and message
            S->>A: Reply — "no longer available. Send full name,<br/>voucher size, and housing authority."
            A->>T: Deliver the team's reply
        else By phone call
            T->>A: Phone call to the app's number
            A->>S: Incoming call
            Note over S: Ignores the call
            A->>T: [AUTO] Auto-reply text — "Send full name,<br/>voucher size, and housing authority."
        end
        T->>A: Full name, voucher size, housing authority
        Note over A: [MANUAL] Save contact<br/>Populate details panel, mark record as Tenant
        A->>S: Relay tenant details
    else In person (housing fair)
        Note over S,T: Goal — house them the same day. Match each person to a property,<br/>then a landlord shows the unit to them (or they go alone) that day.
        alt Team takes their details
            Note over S: A team member sits down with the tenant at the fair
            S->>A: Enter details on the new contact page<br/>(name, voucher size, housing authority)
            Note over A: [MANUAL] Create contact, populate details panel, mark record as Tenant
        else Tenant self-serves
            T->>A: Submit details via the self-serve portal
            Note over A: [AUTO] Contact created from portal submission,<br/>mark record as Tenant
        end
        A->>T: [AUTO] Automatic text message starting the process
    end
    Note over S,A: Eligibility intake — narrow questions for LIF
    S->>A: Pets? Evictions? How long at current place?
    A->>T: Deliver questions
    T->>A: Answers
    A->>S: Relay answers
    S->>A: Do you have an RTA in hand?
    A->>T: Deliver question
    T->>A: RTA status
    Note over A: [MANUAL] Store intake answers, set LIF-eligibility and RTA flags
    A->>S: Relay RTA status
    alt RTA in hand
        Note over T,S: Hand off to Send Unit sequence (separate)
    else No RTA in hand
        Note over S,A: Can't meaningfully help yet — park lead until an RTA is in hand
    end
